        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 5:37PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 537 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurel Hill, or 11 miles west of Florala. This storm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Florala, Lockhart, and Laurel Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
